---
name: 'no-noise'
alwaysApply: true
description: 'Prevent comment/doc/file noise. Keep changes minimal and intentional.'
---

## Output + changes discipline (hard rules)

- Do NOT generate large docs, reports, checklists, summaries, changelogs, deployment guides unless the user explicitly asks.
- Do NOT add new markdown files by default. Prefer updating existing files only.
- Do NOT add "template"/"example" comments. Comments are allowed only for invariants / sharp edges / things easy to break.
- Prefer deleting boilerplate over keeping it "just in case".

## No overengineering (hard rule)

- Do NOT create unnecessary abstractions and wrappers.
